pub6.ezboard.com/ujaes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jaes</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Fruitloop</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>5/12/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>10:00:36 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: plants</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well the whole point was that no matter how sensitive you are, you have to eat a &quot;feeling organism&quot; in order to survive. It's the natural order of things. If you don't like you can always slit your wrists, right?<br>
<br>
The flip side to those sorts of studies about animal emotions is that even though we're finding hormonal changes in their bodies, it's still impossible for us to discern what's actually happening in their minds. They could still very well be automatons, and the endorphins are merely just behavior modifying. They may signify something that is beneficial for the organism, but that doesn't necessarily imply that they actually feel happiness. <br>
<br>
There was a case of a man who had suffered some brain damage and lost his vision in his right eye. He could no longer &quot;see&quot; anything out of it, in the sense that he couldn't experience the mental visual imagery that we normally do when we see. But he could still &quot;sense&quot; out of it. A doctor who was studying him had placed a patch over his good eye to prevent him from seeing, and drew shapes on a dark wall in front of him with a laser pointer. Even though he was not receiving images from his right eye, the eye was still picking up the visual stimulus and he could call out the shape that was being drawn. The man didn't know how he could sense the shapes, he just could. Studies on his brain showed that because of the damage, the signals sent to his brain from his retina were travelling along an ancient passage found in many other species of animals. Instead of traveling to the visual center, they were bypassing it to reach some other part of the brain. <br>
<br>
This whole study sort of implies that animals might not see the world around them the way that we do. They might not look around and describe the world in terms of imagery. Instead they just &quot;feel&quot; the world around them, functioning out of instinctual understanding.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showMessage?topicID=950.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showMessage?topicID=967.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=839.topic&index=695><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.threadControl?topicID=839.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=839.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=839.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Unsubscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</FONT><BR></TD><TD></TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN=3 ALIGN=CENTER><BR><FORM ACTION=http://pub6.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum METHOD=POST><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Jump to: </FONT><SELECT NAME=forumName><OPTION VALUE=namelesstavernthenamelessserverboardru